# Ignore Python virtual environment and cache
    backend/venv/
    backend/__pycache__/

    # NEVER upload database passwords
    backend/.env

    # Next.js already ignores its own files, but just in case:
    frontend/node_modules/
    frontend/.next/
    ```
  
  
    Now tell Git to track this folder, stage all your files (except the ignored ones), and save your first checkpoint:
    ```cmd
    git init
    git add .
    git commit -m "Day 3: Full-stack MVP architecture with database"
    ```
  
  
    Go to [GitHub.com](https://github.com) and log in. 
    1. Click the **+** icon in the top right and select **New repository**.
    2. Name it `marketplace-mvp`.
    3. Leave it **Public** or **Private** (your choice).
    4. **Do not** check the boxes for README, .gitignore, or license (we want it completely empty so it doesn't clash with your local files).
    5. Click **Create repository**.
  
  
    GitHub will show you a page with some terminal commands. Look for the section titled *"…or push an existing repository from the command line"*. Copy those three lines and run them in your terminal. They will look exactly like this (but with your username):
    ```cmd
    git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/marketplace-mvp.git
    git branch -M main
    git push -u origin main
    ```